3. The human is the **user**. The phone, browser, or app is the **client**.
4. Physical servers are expensive to buy, take time to set up, and companies must pay for them even when they are idle.
5. Pay-as-You-Go means I only pay for the AWS resources I actually use. When I stop using them, I stop paying.
6. AWS can increase resources during high demand and reduce them when demand decreases (when services like Auto Scaling are configured).

